06/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The defence ministries of Macedonia and Albania held a forum on NATO integration and the reform of defence systems on Friday (4 April).
Defence ministry official Ljubomir Popovski said Macedonia had achieved significant progress in reforms, adding that regional co-operation in the defence arena was essential to preserving security and stability.
Brig Gen Luan Hoxha represented Albania's Defence Ministry.
Recently, the two countries held their first joint military drill;
another will be held soon.
(Albanian Daily News - 05/04/03, MIA - 04/04/03)
